<paragraph blockId="7.[151,760,190,469]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,328,190,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Molecular data.</emphasis>
<collectionCode box="[332,378,190,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">BIN</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[383,459,190,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">BOLD</collectionCode>
: ACX8837 (n = 6; 3 public, 1 from Altai, 2 from Tuva). The average intraspecific divergence of the barcode region is 0.73% (maximum 1.77%). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,298,286,309]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Distribution.</emphasis>
Palaearctic. In Europe present in 
<collectingCountry box="[657,759,286,309]" name="Lithuania" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Lithuania</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[197,274,318,341]" name="Poland" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Poland</collectingCountry>
, from where it was described as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">E. leucostictellus</emphasis>
(Rebel, 1917). In 
<collectingCountry box="[409,480,350,373]" name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Russia</collectingCountry>
it occurs east of the 
<collectingRegion box="[706,759,350,373]" country="Russia" name="Altay" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Altai</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LVOVSKY A. L." box="[159,317,382,405]" pageId="7" pageNumber="208" pagination="780 - 801" refId="ref27641" refString="LVOVSKY A. L. 2013: A review of flat moths of the genus Exaeretia Stainton, 1849 (Lepidoptera, Depressariidae) of the fauna of Russia and neighbouring countries. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 92: 780 - 801 (in Russian)." type="journal article" year="2013">LVOVSKY 2013</bibRefCitation>
), the only records from the 
<collectingRegion box="[604,759,382,405]" country="Russia" name="Altay" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Altai Republic</collectingRegion>
(Kosh-Agach: Ukok plateau) were published by 
<bibRefCitation author="BIDZILYA O. V. &amp; BUDASHKIN YU &amp; KLYUCHKO Z. F. &amp; KOSTJUK I. &amp; YU" pageId="7" pageNumber="208" pagination="201 - 220" refId="ref26742" refString="BIDZILYA O. V., BUDASHKIN YU. I., KLYUCHKO Z. F. &amp; KOSTJUK I. YU. 2002: A contribution to the knowledge of the Lepidoptera fauna of the Ukok plateau in south-eastern Altai, Russia. Entomofauna, Zeitschrift fur Entomologie 23: 201 - 220." type="journal article" year="2002">BIDZILYA et al. (2002)</bibRefCitation>
. The first record for the 
<collectingRegion box="[541,595,446,469]" country="Russia" name="Tyva" pageId="7" pageNumber="208">Tuva</collectingRegion>
Republic.
</paragraph>
